{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_geranium_ver02/data/sn84028102/00340580813/1957082901/0542.xml":{"full_text":"Geauga Cancer Deaths\nBelow National Rate\nFigures have just been releas\ned by the U. S. Public Health\nService showing the proportion\nof deaths from Lung cancer and\nfrom other forms of cancer in\nGeauga County and in other\nparts of the nation.\nIt comes at a time when there\nU concern, throughout the coun\ntry, over the reported link be\ntween cigarette smoking and\nlung cancer. The American Can\ncer Society has issued data in\ndicating a strong connection be\ntween the two, based on a stu\ndy of 188,000 men.\nHOLD IT!\nBefore you\nsign for a\nsmall\ncar...\nSTARTLING FACT\n5 out of 10 Smaller Cars\nwear a Pontiac Price Tag\n-yet none gives you Any\nof Pontiac\u2019s Advantages\nPONTIAC GIVES YOU UP TO 8.9%\nMORE SOLID CAR PER DOLLAR.\nNot one of the smaller cars can give yor\nthe heavy-duty construction, the\nroad-hugging heft and solid security of\nAmerica\u2019s Number One Road Car!,\nPONTIAC GIVES YOU\n4 TO 7 INCHES MORE WHEELBASE.\nHere\u2019s extra length where it counts\u2014\nto bracket the bumps instead of riding\nthem! And this extra length shows up inside!\ntoo, with plenty of stretch-out\nroom for six-footers!\nPONTIAC\u2019S PERFORMANCE TOPS\nTHE BEST THE SMALL CARS CAN\nOFFER BY A WIDE MARGIN.\nYour Pontiac dealer can give you a\ncomplete facts-and-figures comparison\nand an on-the-road test to prove that Pontiac\nperformance stands head and shoulders\nabove anything in the low-price field!\nAND PONTIAC HAS ALWAYS\nBEEN FAMOUS AS ONE OF\nAMERICA\u2019S TOP TRADE-INS!\nSo why not look and feel like a million\n\u2014instead of a million others?\nTrading's\nTerrific\nRIGHT NOW!\nNOW I If yoo want th* ultimata In bath economy and extraordinary\nperformance, new Trl-Fower Carburetion Is available at extra\ncost on oven the lowest priced Pontiac models I It's America's\nnewest power advance and exclusively Pontiac's at so low cost I\nPontiaca\nSEE YOUR AUTHORIZED\nDEALER\nMore recently, U. S. Surgeon\nGeneral Leroy.Burney corrobor\nated this, stating...\u201cThere is an\nincreasing and consistent body\nof evidence that excessive cig\narette smoking is one of the\ncausative factors in lung can\ncer.\u201d\nThe new Public Health Ser\nvice report shows the extent of\nthis toll in each section of the\nUnited States for the 12 months\nending January, 1956.\nAmong residents of Geauga\nCounty, it found, the number of\ndeaths from cancer and other\nmalignant growths came to 43\nin the year. Of this total, the\nnumber attributed to lung can\ncer was 3, or 7.0 percent.\nNationally, 12.4 percent of all\nCancer mortality was due to\nlung cancer and, in the State of\nOhio. 12.1 percent.\nLocally, the PHS report show\ns, the number of deaths due to\nall forms of cancer was lower,\nin proportion to population, than\nin most sections of the United\nStates. The rate, among local\nresidents was 140 such deaths\nper 100,000 population, as again\nst 145 per 100,000 for the nation.\nIt was lower, also, then that of\nthe State of Ohio, 158 per 100,\n000.\nThe cigarette smoking lung\ncancer problem is causing great\nconcern among the smokers of\nthe country, They stand uncer\ntainly between the pronounce\nments of the health and cancer\ngroups on the one side and the\ncounter-claims of the tobacco\nindustry. The industry contends\nthere is no real evidence of a\nrelationship. The \u201cproof\u201d to\ndate, it claims, is only statisti\ncal, not scientific.\nIn the overall battle against\ncancer, encouraging results are\nreported by the American Can\ncer Society. Today, it states, one\nout of every three people afflict\ned is being saved, compared\nwith only one in four a few years\nago.\n2 Cars Crash\nFriday on 306\nDamage was reported to two\ncars which collided on a section\nof Rt. 306 which is still under\nrepair in Chester Township Fri\nday at 7:30 p.m., according to a\nreport made by Deputy Sheriff\nDavid Yates.\nThe accident occured when a\ncar driven by Eugene Lyons, 30,\nof Chesterland hit a bump in the\nroad and he lost control of the\ncar, sliding sideways into the\nleft lane and colliding with a\ncar driven by Jeanette Ramser,\nalso of Chesterland.\nFenders on both cars were\ndamaged.\nAutos Collide\nin Chester Twp.\nTwo cars were seriously dam\naged when they collided at the\nintersection of Wilson Mills and\nBardwell Rd. in Chester Town\nship August 13, the sheriff\u2019s de\npartment reports.\nRonnie Davis' of Claridon\nRd., Chardon, said he was driv\ning on Wilson Mills Rd. when\nhe noticed the car driven by\nGeoffrey W. Grant, 16, of Chag\nrin Falls, coming out of the in\ntersection.\nDavis said he attempted to a\nvoid the other car, but was un\nable to do so because it was in\nthe middle of the intersection.\nThe\nWelcome Wagon\nHostess\nWill knock on Your Door\nwith Gifts and Greetings\nfrom Friendly Business\nNeighbors and Your\nCivic and Social\nWelfare Leaders\nOn the occasion of\nArrivals of Newcomers to\nCity\nThe Birth of a Baby\nEngagement Announce'\nments\nBetsy Schrader\nChardon 6'5751\nAnn DeMuth\nChardon 6'5315\nHelen Shaffer\nPArk 9'7642\nEleanor Oliver\nMiddlefield, Huntsburg and\nBurton z E. Clar. 6'6485\nAnn Giblin\nNewbury TE 4'8364\nLynette Allin\nPA 9'7530\nk\nMr. and Mrs. James E. Roberts returned to Vene\nzuela last week on the \u201cS.S. Santa Monica\" after thenr\ntwo-month vacation in the United States. Mr. Roberts is\na Cost Accountant with the Creole Petroleum Corpora\ntion, Venzeuelan affiliate of Standard Oil Company (New\u2019\nJersey.) He is located in Lagunillas on the easern shore\nof Lake Maracaibo, one of the richest oil producing areas\nin the world.\nWhile on vacation, the Roberts visited his parents,\nMr. and Mrs. Pearce C. Roberts, in Minneapolis and her\nparents, Mr. and Mrs. Eugene Thomas, Sherman Road,\nChardon, Ohio.\nSEE OUR DISPLAY\nUnder the Grand Stand\nat\nGeauga County Fair\nOpening August 29\nBurr Smith\nFURNITURE\nChardon, Ohio\nbaths a day!\nNew, \u201cfast recovery\u201d electric water heaters produce hot water\nas fast as you can use it. The average 40-gallon model delivers\n72 gallons of hot, hot water in two hours! That\u2019s more than three\ntimes the average family\u2019s daily hot water needs! So if you want\nplenty of hot water\u2014fast, get a \u201cfast recovery\u201d electric water\nheater now.\nA flameless electric water heater costs less to buy up to 40%\nless than any other kind. And you can install it anywhere. Out\nside of heater always stays cool. No flues or vents are needed.\n1\n4-H Sparkies Start\nElectricity Campaign\nThe 4-H Sparkies have started\na campaign to make people a\nware of the danger of electrici\nty. Electricity is dangerous. It\ncan kill. Safety check your home\nelectrical hazards, like frayed\ncords, wrong size fuses and over\nloaded outlets.\nGet full use of electricity. A\nnew house can be crippled too.\nA. Get the power into your\nhouse, a large enough service\nentrance capacity.\nB. Get the power throughout\nSnipper Snappers\nAttend Style Show\nThe members of the 4-H Snip\nper Snappers went to Cleveland\nAugust 15 for a style show. Mrs.\nStanley Newberry drove the\ngirls and advisor to the Rapid\nTransit. The rode the Rapid dwn\nto the terminal. The style show\nwas put on by Seventeen maga\nzine.\nAfter the style show, the girls\nwent to a tea room for a snack.\nThe club gave a preview of\na style show for the county de\nmonstration at Claridon Town\nI Hall August 17.\nHave You Met-\nMr. and Mrs. Gordon Free\nman of 201 Maple St., Chardon?\nThey moved from Wickliffe and\nMr. Freeman is now a partner\nin Geauga Disposal.\nHAVE YOU MET\nMr. and Mrs. Charles Fron\nstin who live on Caves Rd.,\nChesterland? Mr. Fronstln is as\nsistant manager at Paramount\nFinance in Cleveland. They have\none child, Gerry, 3.\n\u25a0ijX\nJ-.\na\nhr\neX-\nK*\nIt's possible with a fast recovery electric water heater\nSpecial Low Rates\nyour house, enough circuits of\nlarge enough wires..\nC. Get the power where you\nwant it, enough outlets, and swi\ntches correctly located.\nThe 4-H Sparkies had a swim\nming party at the home of John\nand Dan Bowyer. Cool weather\ndidn\u2019t stop anyone from having\na pleasant time.\nSee you\nat our\nbooth at\nthe fair!\nWIN A\nPRIZE\nAbsolutely\nFree\n\u201cPhil\u201d Adams\nIt\u2019s safe, clean and completely automatic \u2014nothing to light,\nnothing to \u201cgo out,\u201d nothing to attract curious youngsters.\nThe next meeting will be Aug\nust 23 at the home of the advi\nsor, Harold Newberry. All pro\njects for the fair are to be turn\ned in and books completed.\nMONTVILLE\nSERVICE GARAGE\nAuthorised Kaiser Willys\nSales Service\nLOUIS BURGER\nMontville, Ohio\nJunction Kts. o28 and 86\nPhone Montville 3422\nWRECKER SERVICE\nBox 74 East Claridon\nTelephone East Claridon 66916\nfinest work\nin the nation\nUpholstering, repairs, or custom\nfurniture costs you no more\nfrom us. Our grand national\naward for our work is an ab\nsoulte guarantee of quality. Just\ngive us a telephone call for free\nsuggestions and estimates.\nCRAFTLINE\nMANUACTURING COMPANY\nAl Janossy 3939 Mayfield Rd.\nEVer9reen 2-0800\nor evenings call PArk 9-7914\nwhen you use an electric water heater of\n30-gallon capacity or more. For full information, call your nearest\nIlluminating Company office.\nALWAYS AT YOOI SERVICE IN TIE BEST ^LOCATION IN TIE NATIM","height":"28200","width":"21441"}}
